title.narrative: MATERNAL, NEWBORN, CHILD HEALTH, HIV SERVICES AND IMMUNIZATION

description.narrative: Increased access and use of quality maternal, neonatal and child health care services, including Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission of HIV (PMTCT) and Pediatric ART services, by pregnant and lactating women, neonates and infants particularly in the most deprived geographic areas, including emergency prone provinces and peri-urban Luanda., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Adolescents And Hiv/Aids, Care And Treatment Of Children Affected By Hiv And Aids, Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2019, the most vulnerable children, boys, girls, adolescents and women of child bearing age will have reduced reported common preventable illnesses and disease conditions

description.narrative: An estimated 544,060 (of 742,043) children under five were treated diarrhoea with oral rehydration solution (ORS with zinc) by community development and health agents (ADECOS). All 18 provinces developed their costed prevention of mother to child HIV transmission (PMTCT) expansion plans. More than 4.5 million children received mono-valent type 2 oral polio vaccine in response supplementary vaccination activities to polio-vaccine derived (cVDPVD2) outbreaks. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:17/12/2019
